Olaide Oyelude, Katsina Governor Aminu Masari of Katsina State  on Friday  appointed 13   new special advisers. The  immediate past  Chairman of the Nigeria Labour Congress in the state,Tanimu Saulawa, and former Information and Culture Commissioner, Alhaji Hamza Brodo, made the list. In a statement  by the Secretary to the State Government, Alhaji Mustapha Inuwa, other  new appointees on the list are Alhaji Muntari Lawal, who is also the Permanent Secretary, Government House; Alhaji Kabir Shu’aibu (Political Affairs); Abdulkadir Nasir (Economic Empowerment and Special Intervention); Alhaji Abdullahi Mahuta (Legislative Matters)  and Hussaini Karaduwa (Employment Promotion). Others are Alhaji Abdu Dankum (Rural and Semi-Urban Water Supply); Alhaji Aminu Jibia (Skill Acquisition and Vocational Training) and Alhaji  Lawal Bagiwa (Livestock and Grazing Reserves). The rest are Alhaji Khalil Aminu (Youths); Mohammed  Ruwan-Godiya (Higher Education); and Alhaji Badiru Dayyabu (Inter- Governmental and Developmental Partners). Masari named Saulawa  as his new special adviser on  labour and productivity  and Brodo as his special adviser on narcotics and human trafficking. The governor  said the appointments were based on merit. Copyright PUNCH.
